00:15:03,708 --> 00:15:06,250
Well, so far it looks like a
simple inferiority complex.

243
00:15:06,333 --> 00:15:08,750
He's always being compared to
Honey-senpai so that's why

244
00:15:08,833 --> 00:15:12,000
he feels such animosity towards
him. His older brother is

245
00:15:12,083 --> 00:15:14,833
more attractive, more popular
and a better martial artist

246
00:15:14,916 --> 00:15:17,166
than he is. I think he's
just letting his jealousy

247
00:15:17,250 --> 00:15:18,708
get the best of him.

248
00:15:18,791 --> 00:15:20,875
It's totally normal
and way boring.

249
00:15:20,958 --> 00:15:22,958
We're gonna go find
something more entertaining.

250
00:15:23,041 --> 00:15:24,750
Hold on!
Come back here you two!

251
00:15:24,833 --> 00:15:27,083
Why are you suddenly
being so uncooperative?

252
00:15:27,166 --> 00:15:28,958
Well, we thought
there'd be an interesting,

253
00:15:29,041 --> 00:15:32,250
secret reason they're
fighting. This is just lame.

254
00:15:32,333 --> 00:15:33,791
So Honey-senpai and
Chika's feelings

255
00:15:33,875 --> 00:15:36,041
aren't exciting enough?!

256
00:15:36,125 --> 00:15:38,750
It's okay Tama-chan, really.

257
00:15:38,833 --> 00:15:41,208
But, Honey-senpai.

258
00:15:41,291 --> 00:15:43,916
It's alright;
don't worry about me.

259
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:46,375
So what if
Chika-chan hates me.

260
00:15:46,458 --> 00:15:48,958
I would be happy just seeing
him grow up to be strong

261
00:15:49,041 --> 00:15:51,583
and healthy; he is
my brother after all.

262
00:15:51,666 --> 00:15:54,291
Um, he's already a lot taller
than you Honey-senpai.

263
00:15:54,375 --> 00:15:56,500
Yeah, he's pretty "grown up"
and plenty "healthy".

264
00:15:56,583 --> 00:15:59,666
'Scuse me, could you guys
please keep it down?

265
00:16:01,416 --> 00:16:03,541
What're you doing here?! I
thought I had told you to

266
00:16:03,625 --> 00:16:06,000
stay away from me at
school Mitskuni!

267
00:16:11,833 --> 00:16:13,500
You alien.

268
00:16:13,583 --> 00:16:16,041
Just leave me alone!

269
00:16:16,125 --> 00:16:17,666
But Chika-chan.

270
00:16:17,750 --> 00:16:19,166
What's he mean "alien"?

271
00:16:19,250 --> 00:16:21,291
Why would you call him that?
Just because your brother

272
00:16:21,375 --> 00:16:23,166
is stronger than you are
doesn't give you the right to

273
00:16:23,250 --> 00:16:24,666
call him an alien!

274
00:16:24,750 --> 00:16:28,458
Yeah, why are you so upset
about cake and stuffed animals?

275
00:16:28,541 --> 00:16:31,583
Well If it was just about
the cake and stuffed animals

276
00:16:31,666 --> 00:16:33,583
I would never have
said anything.

277
00:16:35,791 --> 00:16:39,000
Let's get this straight, I
didn't call my brother an alien

278
00:16:39,083 --> 00:16:40,875
because he's stronger than me.

279
00:16:43,916 --> 00:16:46,416
Have any of you ever seen
him devour an entire cake?!

280
00:16:46,500 --> 00:16:48,541
Don't tell me that you guys
think that's perfectly normal!

281
00:16:48,625 --> 00:16:51,208
He has 3 whole cakes after
dinner every night for dessert!

282
00:16:51,291 --> 00:16:55,083
Seriously- three cakes a night!
And he never gains weight!

283
00:16:56,041 --> 00:16:58,500
I humbly accept
this yummy dessert!

284
00:16:59,708 --> 00:17:01,541
That was delicious!

285
00:17:03,041 --> 00:17:05,958
So Honey-senpai eats
that way at home, too?

286
00:17:07,041 --> 00:17:09,416
And then something crazy
occurred last week.

287
00:17:09,500 --> 00:17:12,250
I happened to wake up in
the middle of the night.

288
00:17:12,333 --> 00:17:15,125
And I noticed that the light
was on in the dining room.

289
00:17:16,833 --> 00:17:19,583
What's going on? It's the
middle of the night, you know.

290
00:17:19,666 --> 00:17:22,333
Hey, Chika-chan.

291
00:17:22,416 --> 00:17:25,291
No way! He's eating cake-
at this hour??!

292
00:17:25,375 --> 00:17:28,750
I'm glad you're here. Once a
week I have a special cake

293
00:17:28,833 --> 00:17:32,958
night where I eat all the cake I
want. Usa-chan here helped me

294
00:17:33,041 --> 00:17:35,208
to come up with the idea.

295
00:17:35,291 --> 00:17:38,083
Would you like to join us?

296
00:17:41,500 --> 00:17:43,000
C'mon, be honest.

297
00:17:43,083 --> 00:17:45,083
You know there's no way
a regular human being

298
00:17:45,166 --> 00:17:47,708
can eat that much cake!
Aren't you terrified?!

299
00:17:47,791 --> 00:17:50,041
I bet he gets signals from his
home planet through that weird

300
00:17:50,125 --> 00:17:53,208
bunny of his! Why can't you
see that he's an alien?!

301
00:17:53,291 --> 00:17:54,791
When you think about it-

302
00:17:54,875 --> 00:17:56,791
-everything Chika
just said to us-

303
00:17:56,875 --> 00:18:00,291
-suddenly makes perfect
sense, doesn't it?

304
00:18:00,375 --> 00:18:03,791
I don't know though.
There was a time when Mitskuni

305
00:18:03,875 --> 00:18:05,666
and I got along really well.

306
00:18:05,750 --> 00:18:08,083
While it's true that my
brother's always had a fondness

307
00:18:08,166 --> 00:18:09,916
for cute things and more
of a sweet tooth

308
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:13,333
than I have. I still respected
his ability to avoid

309
00:18:13,416 --> 00:18:16,250
that stuff even though
he loved it.

310
00:18:16,333 --> 00:18:18,958
And then this idiot came
along and brainwashed him

311
00:18:19,041 --> 00:18:21,291
with some ridiculous nonsense.

312
00:18:21,375 --> 00:18:23,500
Something about acknowledging
who you really are

313
00:18:23,583 --> 00:18:28,583
and just being yourself.
That that's true strength!

314
00:18:28,666 --> 00:18:31,541
Not long after that he fell
apart and became the alien

315
00:18:31,625 --> 00:18:33,541
he is today.

316
00:18:33,625 --> 00:18:35,750
Oh, I see, so all
of Chika's troubles-

317
00:18:35,833 --> 00:18:38,541
-can be traced right back to
you, isn't that true boss?

318
00:18:38,625 --> 00:18:40,208
What are you talking about?!
I didn't mean to!

319
00:18:40,291 --> 00:18:41,916
There's gotta be some way
we can fix this!

320
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:43,708
Come on, you guys!

321
00:18:44,958 --> 00:18:46,833
There is a way
to solve this, you know.

322
00:18:46,916 --> 00:18:48,125
You've got it figured out?!

323
00:18:48,208 --> 00:18:51,125
So Mitsukuni,
you know what to do.

324
00:18:52,875 --> 00:18:56,458
Listen, Chika-chan,
I never meant to upset you.

325
00:18:56,541 --> 00:18:58,791
I didn't know that you
hated sweets that much

326
00:18:58,875 --> 00:19:00,166
and I'm very sorry.

327
00:19:00,250 --> 00:19:03,291
Oh no, it looks like he
completely missed the point.

328
00:19:03,375 --> 00:19:05,500
Nobody can make me
change who I am.

329
00:19:05,583 --> 00:19:07,750
I'm really grateful
to Tama-chan and all

330
00:19:07,833 --> 00:19:11,458
of the Host Club because
they've shown me that.

331
00:19:11,541 --> 00:19:13,583
So.

332
00:19:13,666 --> 00:19:17,041
Let's settle this like men,
in the Haninozuka style.

333
00:19:17,125 --> 00:19:18,666
Yasuchika.

334
00:19:28,083 --> 00:19:31,250
Since when does Ouran have
a field like this?

335
00:19:31,333 --> 00:19:35,666
And don't forget Chika-chan,
this is a one-point match.

336
00:19:35,750 --> 00:19:38,000
So what happens if I win?

337
00:19:38,083 --> 00:19:40,041
If you win I'll
stop eating cake

338
00:19:40,125 --> 00:19:41,791
in the middle of the night.

339
00:19:43,958 --> 00:19:45,250
All right.

340
00:19:46,708 --> 00:19:51,375
Are you ready for battle,
men? Then, you may begin.

341
00:20:00,083 --> 00:20:02,583
Is it just me? Or is this
fight turning out exactly like

342
00:20:02,666 --> 00:20:03,875
the one they had earlier?

343
00:20:03,958 --> 00:20:06,500
Yes, but this time
their roles are reversed.

344
00:20:06,583 --> 00:20:08,583
Mitsukuni's already planned
how this entire fight

345
00:20:08,666 --> 00:20:10,458
will pan out.

346
00:20:10,541 --> 00:20:13,708
Yasuchika will attack with
his shuriken any moment now.

347
00:20:15,708 --> 00:20:17,083
Whoa, he called it!

348
00:20:17,166 --> 00:20:20,958
Uh, Mori-senpai, where do
they hide these shuriken?

349
00:20:21,041 --> 00:20:23,916
I have been watching these two
brothers spar for many years.

350
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:25,833
And it didn't take long
before I noticed that

351
00:20:25,916 --> 00:20:28,250
in every match Yasuchika
incorporates moves

352
00:20:28,333 --> 00:20:31,375
that Mitsukuni used
in the previous match.

353
00:20:31,458 --> 00:20:34,291
Mitsukuni realized it as well,
and he always tries to give

354
00:20:34,375 --> 00:20:36,125
his brother the opportunity
to practice

355
00:20:36,208 --> 00:20:38,416
those new techniques.

356
00:20:38,500 --> 00:20:41,125
He may call him an alien,
but as far as martial arts

357
00:20:41,208 --> 00:20:43,625
are concerned, Yasuchika
has a deep respect for

358
00:20:43,708 --> 00:20:46,166
Mitsukuni and his abilities.
I think all he really

359
00:20:46,250 --> 00:20:48,291
wants is to be like his
older brother. They are

360
00:20:48,375 --> 00:20:51,125
connected just as two
siblings ought to be.

361
00:20:51,208 --> 00:20:53,708
And personally, I think
a little sibling rivalry

362
00:20:53,791 --> 00:20:55,375
is perfectly normal.

363
00:20:57,875 --> 00:21:00,916
There's no need to worry about
the outcome of this match.

364
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:03,125
I can already tell you that
Mitsukuni's planning to

365
00:21:03,208 --> 00:21:06,208
throw the fight and let
Yasuchika beat him.

366
00:21:06,291 --> 00:21:09,500
Trust me, I know everything
there is to know about him.

367
00:21:09,583 --> 00:21:11,166
Defend yourself!

368
00:21:17,541 --> 00:21:23,416
Yay! I'm the winner!
Cake! Cake! Cake!

369
00:21:23,500 --> 00:21:26,125
I have an idea! Since I won,
I think we should

370
00:21:26,208 --> 00:21:29,208
start having special cake
night three times a week!

371
00:21:32,958 --> 00:21:36,958
Don't let it get you
down, Mori-senpai.

372
00:21:37,041 --> 00:21:39,166
So Honey-senpai's
love of cake exceeds

373
00:21:39,250 --> 00:21:42,458
his love for his brother.

374
00:21:42,541 --> 00:21:45,375
Man, he's a horrible person.

375
00:21:46,666 --> 00:21:49,375
I would think that embracing
the things you truly like and

376
00:21:49,458 --> 00:21:53,333
being able to enjoy them is
worth more than anything.

377
00:21:53,416 --> 00:21:55,958
To just be yourself.
I believe that's

378
00:21:56,041 --> 00:21:58,250
what true strength really is.

379
00:22:01,333 --> 00:22:03,000
I love you!

380
00:23:13,041 --> 00:23:15,500
What?! The Zuka Club
from Lobelia Academy has

381
00:23:15,583 --> 00:23:18,083
kidnapped Haruhi?!
Don't you worry, Haruhi!

382
00:23:18,166 --> 00:23:20,250
I'm on my way to save you
right this minute!

383
00:23:20,333 --> 00:23:22,875
Next time, "Lobelia Girls'
Academy Strikes Back"!

384
00:23:22,958 --> 00:23:25,416
Until then, the Ouran Host
Club will be waiting for you!

385
00:23:25,500 --> 00:23:26,541
We'll see you then!

